# Pull requests

## Shell: `gh` on PATH + Bash for tokens

**Two issues:** (1) Cursor and some minimal shells omit **`/opt/homebrew/bin`**, so **`gh` is missing** even when Homebrew installed it. (2) **zsh** may not load **`GH_TOKEN`** from your Bash profile.

**Preferred (tokens + Homebrew):** from the repo root, use the wrapper inside a login Bash so both PATH and `GH_TOKEN` apply:

```bash
bash -lc 'cd /path/to/Gestalt && ./scripts/gh pr create --base main --head feature/your-branch --title "..." --body "..."'
bash -lc 'cd /path/to/Gestalt && ./scripts/gh pr list'
bash -lc 'cd /path/to/Gestalt && ./scripts/gh auth status'
```

**If `gh` is already on your PATH** (e.g. after opening a new integrated terminal with **`.vscode/settings.json`**), you can use **`bash -lc 'gh …'`** only.

The repo script **`scripts/gh`** prepends `/opt/homebrew/bin` and `/usr/local/bin` before calling `gh`. **`.vscode/settings.json`** prepends the same for **macOS integrated terminals** in Cursor/VS Code.

Use the same **`bash -lc`** pattern for any CLI that only picks up API keys from Bash login/profile files.

Before `gh pr create` or finalizing a PR, follow **`.cursor/rules/git-workflow.mdc`**: **`git fetch origin`** and **`git pull origin main`** on the PR branch so `main` is integrated and conflicts are resolved locally.

When creating or drafting a pull request for this repository (including via `gh pr create`):

1. Read and follow **`.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`** — the PR title and body must include every section from that template: **Summary**, **Type of change** (checkboxes), **Changes**, **How to test**, and **Checklist** (checkboxes).
2. Fill each section with concrete, accurate detail (what changed, why, how to verify, risk notes). Do not submit a one-line PR description.
3. Prefer `gh pr create --body-file` with a complete body, or paste the filled template into `--body`, so GitHub receives the full structure.

The template is the single source of truth for PR format in this project.
